### What problem does this feature solve?
This could allow extends Store like in Nuxt.JS.
Without that we don't have clean way for use `this.app` of `this.$router` in vuex actions and mutations.

With that we can extends like :
```ts
declare module 'vuex/types/index' {
  interface Store<S> {
    app: Vue;
    $route: Route;
  }
}
```

### What does the proposed API look like?
https://github.com/vuejs/vuex/blob/91f3e69ed9e290cf91f8885c6d5ae2c97fa7ab81/types/index.d.ts#L10 Change type of that from `class` to `interface`

