### What problem does this feature solve?

I have some mutations that need chain reaction in some cases, and for now, I have to hard code `namespace` inside the mutations. But I made this module as far as possible to reuse in other pages, and my project is not SPA, so I have to re-registerModule in every pages. But in some cases, I need to register the module for a different namespace to avoid conflict, and then it will cause error if I have to hard code `namespace` inside the mutations.

For example:
```javascript
function mutation(state, payload) {
    if(payload.situation){
        this.commit("Namespace/CommitFunction", { ... });
    }
    ...
    // Error: [vuex] unknown mutation type: Namespace/CommitFunction
}
```

It may also need to know the namespace in these situation:
* https://github.com/vuejs/vuex/issues/1244

### What does the proposed API look like?
```
function mutation(state, payload, namespace){
    ...
}
```

or

```
function mutation(state, payload){
    console.log(this.namespace);
}
```

